ZH: 交朋友是一种很重要的社交技能。
EN: Making friends is an important social skill.

ZH: 我很喜欢交朋友，因为可以认识到不同的人。
EN: I love making friends because I get to meet different people.

ZH: 他很容易交朋友，每个人都觉得他很友善。
EN: He is very easygoing and makes friends easily; everyone finds him friendly.

ZH: 在新的学校里，她很快就交到了新朋友。
EN: She quickly made new friends at the new school.

ZH: 交朋友不在乎年龄，只要性格合得来就可以。
EN: Making friends is not about age; it's about connecting personalities.

ZH: 有些人很难交朋友，可能是因为性格内向。
EN: Some people find it difficult to make friends, perhaps because they are introverted.

ZH: 我们应该鼓励孩子多去交朋友，从小培养社交能力。
EN: We should encourage children to make more friends and develop social skills from a young age.

ZH: 在大学里，我交到了很多志同道合的朋友。
EN: In college, I made many like-minded friends.

ZH: 她的交朋友能力非常强，所以很快就融入了新的团体。
EN: She has strong social skills, so she quickly integrated into the new group of friends.

ZH: 和不同背景的人交朋友可以拓展我们的视野。
EN: Making friends with people from different backgrounds can broaden our horizons.

ZH: 她认为交朋友是一种很美好的经历。
EN: She considers making friends a wonderful experience.

ZH: 我们每个人都应该感恩身边的朋友，因为是他们让生活更加丰富。
EN: We should all be grateful for the friends around us, as they make our lives richer.

ZH: 交朋友需要真诚和信任。
EN: Making friends requires sincerity and trust.

ZH: 在这个社会中，交朋友是一种非常普遍的行为。
EN: Making friends is a very common behavior in this society.

ZH: 小孩子很容易交到朋友，因为他们天真无邪。
EN: Children easily make friends because they are innocent.

ZH: 他的真诚和友善让他在学校里交到了很多朋友。
EN: His sincerity and kindness have helped him make many friends at school.

ZH: 交朋友可以增加生活的乐趣。
EN: Making friends can add joy to life.

ZH: 有时候，交朋友也会有一些挫折，但重要的是要坚持下去。
EN: Sometimes making friends can be challenging, but it's important to persevere.

ZH: 作为朋友，我们应该互相支持和理解。
EN: As friends, we should support and understand each other.
